100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 16, 1925, news from the global stage highlighted the ongoing tensions in the Middle East, as British forces remained engaged in efforts to stabilize the region amid increasing unrest. In Europe, the aftermath of World War I continued to shape political landscapes, with Germany facing economic challenges and hyperinflation. Meanwhile, in the United States, discussions regarding Prohibition persisted, as debates over its effectiveness grew louder among citizens and lawmakers alike.
